{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645316","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645316"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:15:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:15:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18106"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18106","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18106"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10820"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73541"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10820","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10820"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18106"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59010"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7395"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25184"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25187"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73541","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73541"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures forms the posterior axillary border?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pectoralis major and minor","Subscapularis, teres major, latissimus dorsi","Serratus anterior overlying ribs 1-4","Bicipital groove and biceps heads","Coracobrachialis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe posterior axillary border is formed by the \u003Cstrong\u003Esubscapularis, teres major, and latissimus dorsi\u003C/strong\u003E muscles. These muscles are located at the back of the axilla and play a role in the movement and stability of the shoulder joint.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Epectoralis major and minor\u003C/strong\u003E muscles form the anterior axillary border, not the posterior.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eserratus anterior\u003C/strong\u003E muscle, which overlies ribs 1-4, is located on the lateral thoracic wall and is not part of the posterior axillary border.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebicipital groove and biceps heads\u003C/strong\u003E are part of the anterior aspect of the arm and shoulder, not the posterior axillary border.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecoracobrachialis\u003C/strong\u003E muscle is located in the anterior compartment of the arm and does not contribute to the posterior axillary border.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The posterior axillary border is formed by the subscapularis, teres major, and latissimus dorsi muscles.","Understanding the anatomy of the axillary region is crucial for clinical assessments and surgical procedures."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskelet